dcterms:description: The CREMI dataset is used for evaluating interpolation methods on electron microscopic images. It is divided into three sub-datasets, each containing triplets of consecutive EM images processed for training.
dcterms:title: CREMI Dataset

dcterms:description: cremi triplet A is a subset of the CREMI dataset, consisting of triplets of consecutive EM images processed for training interpolation algorithms.
dcterms:title: cremi triplet A

dcterms:description: cremi triplet B is another subset of the CREMI dataset, containing triplets of consecutive EM images used for evaluating interpolation methods.
dcterms:title: cremi triplet B

dcterms:description: cremi triplet C is the third subset of the CREMI dataset, consisting of triplets of consecutive EM images for training interpolation algorithms.
dcterms:title: cremi triplet C
